From cf4e5534064b12a6713b3142b1cd64b0afa1bd2d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 17:44:45 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] sdl3-dos: opt into SDL_HINT_DOS_PIN_WINDOW_TO_NATIVE_MODE
 (lever 0b)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 9 lever 0b NXEngine-side companion to patches/SDL/0012.

Sets SDL_HINT_DOS_PIN_WINDOW_TO_NATIVE_MODE="1" at OVERRIDE priority
before SDL_Init, identical shape to the existing
SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER / SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP /
SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB setters in the same #ifdef NXE_DOS block.

Effect: SDL3-DOS backend's DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode rejects any mode-set
request whose dimensions differ from the active mode (returning success
without doing a hardware mode change). On Cirrus + UNIVBE — the user's
current real-HW target, where 320×240 VBE modes exist natively
(/tmp/cirrus/SDLDBG.LOG lines 99-125: modes 0x01D9, 0x01F8, etc.) —
this prevents the destructive mode-set #3 to 640×480 that SDL3's
window/fullscreen reconciliation otherwise fires after the engine's
SDL_CreateWindow(320, 240, FULLSCREEN) negotiated mode 0x0136 / similar
at mode-set #1.

Wave 2 DOSBox-X smoke (build/stage/SDLDBG.LOG, 2026-04-26) showed the
unsuppressed sequence and the upper-left rendering bug it produced:

  mode-set #1 (entry): requested id=0x0136 320x240
  mode-set #1 (exit ok)
  ... renderer created against 320×240 surface ...
  mode-set #3 (entry): requested id=0x0111 640x480
  mode-set #3 (exit ok)
  DOSVESA-FB-INIT: ... vram_w=640 vram_h=480 fb_size=614400
  flip-probe: window_size=320x240 framebuffer_pixels=320x240 logical_present=320x240

(Renderer at 320×240, framebuffer at 640×480 — backbuffer-to-VRAM copy
draws into upper-left only, leaves the rest as garbage.) With this
patch + SDL/0012 the third mode-set logs as suppressed and the
framebuffer stays at 320×240 dimensions for the duration of the run.

Why DOS needs this
------------------

DOS-only hint that targets the SDL3-DOS backend specifically. Has no
effect on non-DOS builds. Guarded by NXE_DOS to keep desktop behaviour
unchanged.

Layered with patches/SDL/0011 (lazy fb_state re-init) which still
applies — the lazy re-init is a no-op when the dimensions don't change,
so the two patches compose correctly.

On Mach64 + M64VBE (no native 320×240 modes — chip lacks line-doubling)
this hint is harmless: mode-set #1 already picks the 640×480 fallback
so the suppression gate never triggers. The Mach64 stretch case (renderer
at 320×240 + framebuffer at 640×480) needs a separate stretch-on-flush
fix; deferred to a future wave per the Phase 9 lever 0b scoping.

See docs/PHASE9-15FPS-PLAN.md §3 Lever 0b for the full lever stack.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/main.cpp | 34 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 34 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/main.cpp b/src/main.cpp
index a161313..7652352 100644
--- a/src/main.cpp
+++ b/src/main.cpp
@@ -401,6 +401,40 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[])
   // the LFB code path (the wave-1 / Phase 8 attempt's failure mode).
   // See docs/PHASE9-15FPS-PLAN.md §3 Lever 1 and docs/PHASE8-FINDINGS.md.
   SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB, "1", SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
+
+  // Patch 0046 (Phase 9 lever 0b, 2026-04-26): pin SDL3-DOS to whatever
+  // mode the first SetDisplayMode picks and refuse subsequent dimension
+  // changes. SDL3's window/fullscreen reconciliation in SDL_video.c
+  // (SDL_UpdateFullscreenMode) fires a second mode-set that asks for the
+  // display's desktop mode (SDL3-DOS hard-codes 640×480 in
+  // DOSVESA_VideoInit). On a card with native 320×240 VBE modes (e.g.
+  // Cirrus + UNIVBE — see Cirrus wave-1 capture, /tmp/cirrus/SDLDBG.LOG
+  // lines 99-125 confirming 0x01D9 / 0x01F8 etc), the renderer is created
+  // against the 320×240 surface; the second mode-set bumps VRAM dimensions
+  // to 640×480 but the renderer's backbuffer stays 320×240, producing the
+  // upper-left-only rendering bug surfaced in build/stage/SDLDBG.LOG
+  // 2026-04-26 wave 2 (mode-set #1 320×240 → mode-set #3 640×480 → flip
+  // probe shows window_size=320×240 framebuffer_pixels=320×240 logical=320×240
+  // but DOSVESA-FB-INIT logged vram_w=640 vram_h=480 fb_size=614400).
+  //
+  // The new hint SDL_HINT_DOS_PIN_WINDOW_TO_NATIVE_MODE (added by
+  // patches/SDL/0012) instructs the SDL3-DOS backend's
+  // DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode to suppress mode-changes that would alter
+  // VRAM dimensions, returning success without doing the hardware mode
+  // change. The first mode (whatever the closest match for our 320×240
+  // CreateWindow request was) stays active for the duration of the
+  // process; SDL3 framework state thinks fullscreen succeeded so the
+  // rest of window setup is happy.
+  //
+  // On hardware that has no native 320×240 mode (Mach64 + M64VBE — the
+  // chip lacks line-doubling per the gateway4 wave-1 UNIVBE capture),
+  // mode-set #1 already picks the 640×480 fallback so the suppression
+  // never triggers. Harmless on that target.
+  //
+  // See docs/PHASE9-15FPS-PLAN.md §3 Lever 0b for the full discovery
+  // context (UNIVBE/Cirrus path) and the Mach64-side stretch fix
+  // (deferred to a future wave).
+  SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_DOS_PIN_WINDOW_TO_NATIVE_MODE, "1", SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
 #endif
 
   // SDL3: SDL_Init returns bool (true on success); old `< 0` check would always be false.
